Boil a #medium-sized pot{} of water in preparation for your @pearl barley{1/4}. Rinse your @red split lentils{1/4} thoroughly. Peel and finely chop @onion{1/2}(peeled and finely chopped) and the @carrot{1}(peeled and finely chopped). Finely chop the @celery stick{1}(finely chopped) and roughly chop the @chestnut mushrooms{1}(roughly chopped).

Cook the pearl barley in the boiling water with @salt{1/4%tsp} for around ~{20-25%minutes}, or until soft enough to eat. Once the pearl barley is ready, drain it, rinse it thoroughly and keep it to the side.

Cook off the onions, carrot and celery in a #non-stick saucepan{} on medium heat with @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{1/4%tsp} and cook for around ~{5%minutes} to soften the ingredients.

Add in the @rosemary{2}(sprigs) and @thyme{2}(sprigs) along with the @bay leaf{1} and @tomato purée{2} and cook for a few mins before adding the lentils, mushrooms, half the @vegetable stock pot{1/2} and @water{400%ml}. Drain and rinse the @butter beans{1}(drained and rinsed) and add to the #pan{}, then bring to a simmer and bubble away for ~{15%minutes}.

Chop the @flat leaf parsley{3}(chopped) finely and mix half of this into the @self raising flour{50%g} and @vegetarian suet{50%g} with @salt{1/4%tsp}. Gradually add in @warm water{2-3%tbsp} and mix with your hands until you have a nice soft (yet fairly dry) dough.

Form your dough into small golf ball sized dumplings. Take the lid off the cassoulet and add the rest of your parsley. Strain your pearl barley and add this to the pan too. Stir, then gently add your dumplings to the pan. Cook for ~{10%minutes} on low heat with the lid on.

Test the cassoulet for seasoning and add a little more @salt{} and @black pepper{} if you need to. Ladle it out and start tucking in!